body:
This will throw an error if we search for a book that has no authors.  You can replicate this by typing in "dog" or "test" for example.  You will get the following error in your logcat:

> org.json.JSONException: No value for authors

We can check if a JSONObject has a field or not by using the `.has()` method.  We can use that method to make sure we don't try to grab a value that doesn't exist.

    if(volumeInfo.has("authors")){
        //parse here
    }

like that!

Another option is to use `optJSONArray()` instead of `getJSONArray()`.  This method is used to parse fields that may or may not be present, and won't throw a `JSONException` if it is not present :smile:
